  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is designed to evaluate and compare the efficacy and cost effectiveness of 3
      smoking cessation treatments with HIV-positive cigarette smokers. The treatments include
      face-to-face individual counseling, a computer-Internet-based self-help treatment and a
      self-help manual treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
